<doc id="1334041" wikidata="Q1134174" url="?curid=1334041" title="Gliese 623">
<text>Gliese 623 is a dim double star 25.6 light years from Earth in the constellation Hercules. It was photographed by the NASA/ESA Hubble Space Telescope&#x27;s Faint Object Camera in 1994. The binary system consists of two red dwarfs orbiting each other at a distance of 1.9 astronomical units.

